### IntelliJ IDEA ###
# Allow-list (deny-by-default): only project-level config that is portable and
# shared goes into the repo; everything else in .idea/ (personal workspace
# state, DB credentials, plugin junk, Maven-generated project model) stays
# ignored. A fully-ignored directory cannot have children re-included, hence
# `.idea/*` instead of `.idea`.
.idea/*
!.idea/codeStyles/
!.idea/inspectionProfiles/
!.idea/runConfigurations/
!.idea/checkstyle-idea.xml
!.idea/PMDPlugin.xml
!.idea/palantir-java-format.xml
!.idea/codeInsightSettings.xml
!.idea/vcs.xml
!.idea/encodings.xml
!.idea/externalDependencies.xml
!.idea/sonarlint.xml
*.iws
*.iml
*.ipr

